{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JpgqWGHzdcZm4J5TPooveX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* TB03: Transient Step Response — Slew rate (large-signal)\n     2→* 500mV step to force current-limited slewing\n     3→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     4→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     5→\n     6→Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\n     7→Vbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\n     8→Vbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\n     9→Vbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\n    10→Vbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n    11→\n    12→* 500mV step: 0.5V to 1.0V at t=10us, unity-gain feedback\n    13→Vinp vinp 0 PULSE(0.5 1.0 10u 1n 1n 50u 100u)\n    14→Xota vinp vout vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    15→CL vout 0 10p\n    16→\n    17→.tran 10n 80u\n    18→\n    19→.control\n    20→run\n    21→\n    22→* Measure slew rate using derivative at steepest point\n    23→* Find max derivative during the rising edge (10u to 40u window)\n    24→let dvdt = deriv(v(vout))\n    25→* Restrict to the slewing window\n    26→let t_vec = time\n    27→let sr_max = 0\n    28→\n    29→* Use measurements for the two-crossing method as backup\n    30→* Measure time when output crosses 0.6V and 0.8V during rise\n    31→meas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.6 RISE=1\n    32→meas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.8 RISE=1\n    33→\n    34→echo \"t_low = $&t_low\"\n    35→echo \"t_high = $&t_high\"\n    36→echo \"v_low = 0.6\"\n    37→echo \"v_high = 0.8\"\n    38→\n    39→* Also measure v_before/v_after for t10/t90 fallback\n    40→meas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u\n    41→meas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u\n    42→\n    43→let step = v_after - v_before\n    44→let v_10 = v_before + 0.1 * step\n    45→let v_90 = v_before + 0.9 * step\n    46→\n    47→meas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_10 RISE=1\n    48→meas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_90 RISE=1\n    49→\n    50→echo \"t10 = $&t10\"\n    51→echo \"t90 = $&t90\"\n    52→echo \"v_before = $&v_before\"\n    53→echo \"v_after = $&v_after\"\n    54→\n    55→* Direct SR measurement: max dV/dt in slewing window\n    56→meas tran sr_meas MAX deriv(v(vout)) FROM=10u TO=40u\n    57→\n    58→echo \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"\n    59→\n    60→quit\n    61→.endc\n    62→.end\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"e526a04c-f5c4-4cac-98b8-67fcf43f4096","timestamp":"2026-03-23T10:48:14.272Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice","content":"* TB03: Transient Step Response — Slew rate (large-signal)\n* 500mV step to force current-limited slewing\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* 500mV step: 0.5V to 1.0V at t=10us, unity-gain feedback\nVinp vinp 0 PULSE(0.5 1.0 10u 1n 1n 50u 100u)\nXota vinp vout vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 80u\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Measure slew rate using derivative at steepest point\n* Find max derivative during the rising edge (10u to 40u window)\nlet dvdt = deriv(v(vout))\n* Restrict to the slewing window\nlet t_vec = time\nlet sr_max = 0\n\n* Use measurements for the two-crossing method as backup\n* Measure time when output crosses 0.6V and 0.8V during rise\nmeas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.6 RISE=1\nmeas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.8 RISE=1\n\necho \"t_low = $&t_low\"\necho \"t_high = $&t_high\"\necho \"v_low = 0.6\"\necho \"v_high = 0.8\"\n\n* Also measure v_before/v_after for t10/t90 fallback\nmeas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u\nmeas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u\n\nlet step = v_after - v_before\nlet v_10 = v_before + 0.1 * step\nlet v_90 = v_before + 0.9 * step\n\nmeas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_10 RISE=1\nmeas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_90 RISE=1\n\necho \"t10 = $&t10\"\necho \"t90 = $&t90\"\necho \"v_before = $&v_before\"\necho \"v_after = $&v_after\"\n\n* Direct SR measurement: max dV/dt in slewing window\nmeas tran sr_meas MAX deriv(v(vout)) FROM=10u TO=40u\n\necho \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n","numLines":63,"startLine":1,"totalLines":63}}}
