{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JChVzxrtPQ2HxzmdQyVj1o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014ceLW9M5cBnJDzpEndSqZk","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice","content":"* TB03: Transient Step Response — Slew rate (large-signal)\n* 500mV step to force current-limited slewing\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* 500mV step: 0.5V to 1.0V at t=10us, unity-gain feedback\nVinp vinp 0 PULSE(0.5 1.0 10u 1n 1n 50u 100u)\nXota vinp vout vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 80u\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Compute derivative vector, then measure its max during slewing window\nlet dvdt = deriv(v(vout))\nmeas tran sr_meas MAX dvdt FROM=10u TO=40u\n\necho \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"\n\n* Also provide two-crossing method as backup\n* Output goes from ~0.62V to ~0.99V, so use 0.7V and 0.9V crossings\nmeas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.7 RISE=1\nmeas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.9 RISE=1\n\necho \"t_low = $&t_low\"\necho \"t_high = $&t_high\"\necho \"v_low = 0.7\"\necho \"v_high = 0.9\"\n\n* Also 10-90% fallback\nmeas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u\nmeas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u\n\nlet step = v_after - v_before\nlet v_10 = v_before + 0.1 * step\nlet v_90 = v_before + 0.9 * step\n\nmeas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_10 RISE=1\nmeas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_90 RISE=1\n\necho \"t10 = $&t10\"\necho \"t90 = $&t90\"\necho \"v_before = $&v_before\"\necho \"v_after = $&v_after\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":656,"cache_read_input_tokens":43057,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":656},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"7eb39e22-7b45-424f-bb5c-d60091368d2b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ceLW9M5cBnJDzpEndSqZk","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"ff80a85d-f104-47d4-88bf-5ee7873449e6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T10:49:21.861Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice","content":"* TB03: Transient Step Response — Slew rate (large-signal)\n* 500mV step to force current-limited slewing\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* 500mV step: 0.5V to 1.0V at t=10us, unity-gain feedback\nVinp vinp 0 PULSE(0.5 1.0 10u 1n 1n 50u 100u)\nXota vinp vout vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 80u\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Compute derivative vector, then measure its max during slewing window\nlet dvdt = deriv(v(vout))\nmeas tran sr_meas MAX dvdt FROM=10u TO=40u\n\necho \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"\n\n* Also provide two-crossing method as backup\n* Output goes from ~0.62V to ~0.99V, so use 0.7V and 0.9V crossings\nmeas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.7 RISE=1\nmeas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.9 RISE=1\n\necho \"t_low = $&t_low\"\necho \"t_high = $&t_high\"\necho \"v_low = 0.7\"\necho \"v_high = 0.9\"\n\n* Also 10-90% fallback\nmeas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u\nmeas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u\n\nlet step = v_after - v_before\nlet v_10 = v_before + 0.1 * step\nlet v_90 = v_before + 0.9 * step\n\nmeas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_10 RISE=1\nmeas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_90 RISE=1\n\necho \"t10 = $&t10\"\necho \"t90 = $&t90\"\necho \"v_before = $&v_before\"\necho \"v_after = $&v_after\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":19,"oldLines":24,"newStart":19,"newLines":23,"lines":[" .control"," run"," ","-* Measure slew rate using derivative at steepest point","-* Find max derivative during the rising edge (10u to 40u window)","+* Compute derivative vector, then measure its max during slewing window"," let dvdt = deriv(v(vout))","-* Restrict to the slewing window","-let t_vec = time","-let sr_max = 0","+meas tran sr_meas MAX dvdt FROM=10u TO=40u"," ","-* Use measurements for the two-crossing method as backup","-* Measure time when output crosses 0.6V and 0.8V during rise","-meas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.6 RISE=1","-meas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.8 RISE=1","+echo \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\""," ","+* Also provide two-crossing method as backup","+* Output goes from ~0.62V to ~0.99V, so use 0.7V and 0.9V crossings","+meas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.7 RISE=1","+meas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.9 RISE=1","+"," echo \"t_low = $&t_low\""," echo \"t_high = $&t_high\"","-echo \"v_low = 0.6\"","-echo \"v_high = 0.8\"","+echo \"v_low = 0.7\"","+echo \"v_high = 0.9\""," ","-* Also measure v_before/v_after for t10/t90 fallback","+* Also 10-90% fallback"," meas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u"," meas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u"," "]},{"oldStart":52,"oldLines":11,"newStart":51,"newLines":6,"lines":[" echo \"v_before = $&v_before\""," echo \"v_after = $&v_after\""," ","-* Direct SR measurement: max dV/dt in slewing window","-meas tran sr_meas MAX deriv(v(vout)) FROM=10u TO=40u","-","-echo \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"","-"," quit"," .endc"," .end"]}],"originalFile":"* TB03: Transient Step Response — Slew rate (large-signal)\n* 500mV step to force current-limited slewing\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* 500mV step: 0.5V to 1.0V at t=10us, unity-gain feedback\nVinp vinp 0 PULSE(0.5 1.0 10u 1n 1n 50u 100u)\nXota vinp vout vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 80u\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Measure slew rate using derivative at steepest point\n* Find max derivative during the rising edge (10u to 40u window)\nlet dvdt = deriv(v(vout))\n* Restrict to the slewing window\nlet t_vec = time\nlet sr_max = 0\n\n* Use measurements for the two-crossing method as backup\n* Measure time when output crosses 0.6V and 0.8V during rise\nmeas tran t_low WHEN v(vout)=0.6 RISE=1\nmeas tran t_high WHEN v(vout)=0.8 RISE=1\n\necho \"t_low = $&t_low\"\necho \"t_high = $&t_high\"\necho \"v_low = 0.6\"\necho \"v_high = 0.8\"\n\n* Also measure v_before/v_after for t10/t90 fallback\nmeas tran v_before FIND v(vout) AT=9.9u\nmeas tran v_after FIND v(vout) AT=60u\n\nlet step = v_after - v_before\nlet v_10 = v_before + 0.1 * step\nlet v_90 = v_before + 0.9 * step\n\nmeas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_10 RISE=1\nmeas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=$&v_90 RISE=1\n\necho \"t10 = $&t10\"\necho \"t90 = $&t90\"\necho \"v_before = $&v_before\"\necho \"v_after = $&v_after\"\n\n* Direct SR measurement: max dV/dt in slewing window\nmeas tran sr_meas MAX deriv(v(vout)) FROM=10u TO=40u\n\necho \"sr_meas = $&sr_meas\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n"}}
