{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014mDgYMmuPeafrmSwNYbWVN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YQatP3FcFr6H61ywkvgJLr","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_noise.spice","content":"* TB04: Input-Referred Noise Analysis\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.59\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* AC stimulus on Vinp for noise reference\nVinp vinp 0 dc 0.9 ac 1\n\n* Loop-breaking for open-loop measurement\nLbreak vout vinn 1G\nCdc vinn 0 1\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n* Noise analysis: 50 pts/decade, 1Hz to 1MHz (6 decades = 300 pts)\n* Index 150 = 1kHz, Index 200 = 10kHz\n.noise v(vout) Vinp dec 50 1 1e6\n\n.control\nrun\n\nsetplot noise1\nlet n1k = inoise_spectrum[150]\nlet n10k = inoise_spectrum[200]\n\necho \"noise_1k = $&n1k\"\necho \"noise_10k = $&n10k\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":928,"cache_read_input_tokens":56300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":928},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"080283e5-9b5a-433b-8a33-ba152a8f8623"}
