{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019rWLPmdNJpoigM8bkrHDaa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* TB06: CMRR — Common-Mode Rejection Ratio\n     2→* Both inputs see same AC signal (common-mode)\n     3→* CMRR = Adm_dB - Acm_dB at DC\n     4→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     5→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     6→\n     7→Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\n     8→Vbn  vbn  0 dc 0.634\n     9→Vbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\n    10→Vbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\n    11→Vbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n    12→\n    13→* Common-mode AC source\n    14→Vcm vcm 0 dc 0.9 ac 1\n    15→\n    16→* vinp directly connected to vcm\n    17→* vinn: DC from output via inductor, AC from vcm via coupling cap\n    18→Lbreak vout vinn 1G\n    19→Cac vcm vinn 1\n    20→\n    21→Xota vcm vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    22→CL vout 0 10p\n    23→\n    24→.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n    25→\n    26→.control\n    27→run\n    28→\n    29→* Common-mode gain at DC (1Hz proxy)\n    30→meas ac acm_dc FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n    31→\n    32→* Need differential gain for CMRR computation\n    33→* Run second sim with differential stimulus\n    34→alter Vcm ac = 0\n    35→* Create differential stimulus: need AC on vinp only\n    36→* But vinp is tied to vcm node. Use alter to change.\n    37→* Alternative: compute using known gain from Gate 2\n    38→\n    39→* For now, use the DC gain measured in Gate 2 (~63.5 dB)\n    40→* This is the low-freq differential gain\n    41→let adm_dc = 63.5\n    42→let cmrr = adm_dc - acm_dc\n    43→\n    44→echo \"acm_dc = $&acm_dc\"\n    45→echo \"cmrr_dc = $&cmrr\"\n    46→\n    47→quit\n    48→.endc\n    49→.end\n    50→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"870aa393-293a-434e-bb6e-7f62d69983f5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T11:28:20.415Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_cmrr.spice","content":"* TB06: CMRR — Common-Mode Rejection Ratio\n* Both inputs see same AC signal (common-mode)\n* CMRR = Adm_dB - Acm_dB at DC\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.634\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.88\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.73\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.475\n\n* Common-mode AC source\nVcm vcm 0 dc 0.9 ac 1\n\n* vinp directly connected to vcm\n* vinn: DC from output via inductor, AC from vcm via coupling cap\nLbreak vout vinn 1G\nCac vcm vinn 1\n\nXota vcm vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Common-mode gain at DC (1Hz proxy)\nmeas ac acm_dc FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n\n* Need differential gain for CMRR computation\n* Run second sim with differential stimulus\nalter Vcm ac = 0\n* Create differential stimulus: need AC on vinp only\n* But vinp is tied to vcm node. Use alter to change.\n* Alternative: compute using known gain from Gate 2\n\n* For now, use the DC gain measured in Gate 2 (~63.5 dB)\n* This is the low-freq differential gain\nlet adm_dc = 63.5\nlet cmrr = adm_dc - acm_dc\n\necho \"acm_dc = $&acm_dc\"\necho \"cmrr_dc = $&cmrr\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":50}}}
