{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LcwM4E9yxHxAwoWk3ARj5k","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 8 testbench files have been updated. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n**Files updated (all in `/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/`):**\n\n- `tb_corner_tt.spice`\n- `tb_corner_ss.spice`\n- `tb_corner_ff.spice`\n- `tb_corner_sf.spice`\n- `tb_corner_fs.spice`\n- `tb_temp_-40.spice`\n- `tb_temp_27.spice`\n- `tb_temp_85.spice`\n\n**Change in each file:** Replaced the 4 fixed bias voltage sources (`Vbn`, `Vbcn`, `Vbp`, `Vbcp`) with self-biasing circuitry consisting of:\n\n- **vbn**: 500nA ideal current source into a diode-connected NMOS (W=3.8u L=14u)\n- **vbcn**: 263nA through a stacked cascode NMOS pair (W=2u L=14u on top, W=2.15u L=14u on bottom driven by vbn)\n- **vbp**: 24.3nA through a diode-connected PMOS (W=0.42u L=20u)\n- **vbcp**: 259nA through a stacked cascode PMOS pair (W=0.42u L=2u on top, W=0.42u L=20u on bottom driven by vbp)\n\nEverything else (`.lib` corner selection, `.temp` directives, `.include`, `.ac` analysis, `.control` block with measurements) was preserved unchanged."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8aef614d8a483654 (use SendMessage with to: 'a8aef614d8a483654' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26680\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 88236</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"1869a47a-483e-4b60-90a8-53dc7e6668f6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T11:39:08.023Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Update the 5 corner testbench files in /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/ (tb_corner_tt.spice, tb_corner_ss.spice, tb_corner_ff.spice, tb_corner_sf.spice, tb_corner_fs.spice) to use self-biasing instead of fixed bias voltages.\n\nRead tb_corner_tt.spice first to understand the current format.\n\nThe problem: fixed bias voltages (Vbn=0.65, Vbcn=0.88, Vbp=0.73, Vbcp=0.475) don't work across process corners. At FS and SF corners, the OTA rails because the tail current is wrong.\n\nThe fix: replace the fixed voltage sources for bias with current-source-driven diode-connected transistors that track the process corner.\n\nFor each corner testbench, replace the bias section with:\n\n```spice\n* Self-biasing — tracks process corner\n* vbn: 500nA through diode-connected NMOS (same as M11)\nIbias_n vdd vbn dc 500n\nXbias_n vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.8u L=14u nf=1\n\n* vbcn: cascode reference — 263nA through stacked NMOS\nIbias_cn vdd vbcn dc 263n\nXbias_cn vbcn vbcn bias_mid 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1\nXbias_cs bias_mid vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=14u nf=1\n\n* vbp: 24.3nA through diode-connected PMOS (same as fold instance)\nIbias_p vbp 0 dc 24.3n\nXbias_p vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n\n* vbcp: cascode reference — 259nA through stacked PMOS\nIbias_cp vbcp 0 dc 259n\nXbias_cp vbcp vbcp pbias_mid vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\nXbias_fp pbias_mid vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n```\n\nRemove the old fixed voltage sources (Vbn, Vbcn, Vbp, Vbcp).\n\nKeep everything else the same (the .lib corner line, .include, .ac, .control, measurements).\n\nThe 3 temperature testbenches (tb_temp_-40.spice, tb_temp_27.spice, tb_temp_85.spice) should also get the same self-biasing treatment since bias voltages also shift with temperature.\n\nWrite each file using the Write tool. Read each file first before writing.","agentId":"a8aef614d8a483654","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 8 testbench files have been updated. Here is a summary of what was done:\n\n**Files updated (all in `/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/`):**\n\n- `tb_corner_tt.spice`\n- `tb_corner_ss.spice`\n- `tb_corner_ff.spice`\n- `tb_corner_sf.spice`\n- `tb_corner_fs.spice`\n- `tb_temp_-40.spice`\n- `tb_temp_27.spice`\n- `tb_temp_85.spice`\n\n**Change in each file:** Replaced the 4 fixed bias voltage sources (`Vbn`, `Vbcn`, `Vbp`, `Vbcp`) with self-biasing circuitry consisting of:\n\n- **vbn**: 500nA ideal current source into a diode-connected NMOS (W=3.8u L=14u)\n- **vbcn**: 263nA through a stacked cascode NMOS pair (W=2u L=14u on top, W=2.15u L=14u on bottom driven by vbn)\n- **vbp**: 24.3nA through a diode-connected PMOS (W=0.42u L=20u)\n- **vbcp**: 259nA through a stacked cascode PMOS pair (W=0.42u L=2u on top, W=0.42u L=20u on bottom driven by vbp)\n\nEverything else (`.lib` corner selection, `.temp` directives, `.include`, `.ac` analysis, `.control` block with measurements) was preserved unchanged."}],"totalDurationMs":88236,"totalTokens":26680,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9397,"cache_read_input_tokens":16873,"output_tokens":409,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9397},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
