{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VnkETCWMKDikRENtLiYRsv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* TB: AC Open-Loop Analysis - TT Corner\n     2→* Uses loop-breaking inductor technique\n     3→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     4→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     5→\n     6→.param vdd_val = 1.8\n     7→.param vcm_val = 0.9\n     8→\n     9→Vdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\n    10→\n    11→* Self-biasing — tracks process corner\n    12→* vbn: 500nA through diode-connected NMOS (same as M11)\n    13→Ibias_n vdd vbn dc 500n\n    14→Xbias_n vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.8u L=14u nf=1\n    15→\n    16→* vbcn: cascode reference — 263nA through stacked NMOS\n    17→Ibias_cn vdd vbcn dc 263n\n    18→Xbias_cn vbcn vbcn bias_mid 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1\n    19→Xbias_cs bias_mid vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=14u nf=1\n    20→\n    21→* vbp: 24.3nA through diode-connected PMOS (same as fold instance)\n    22→Ibias_p vbp 0 dc 24.3n\n    23→Xbias_p vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n    24→\n    25→* vbcp: cascode reference — 259nA through stacked PMOS\n    26→Ibias_cp vbcp 0 dc 259n\n    27→Xbias_cp vbcp vbcp pbias_mid vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\n    28→Xbias_fp pbias_mid vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n    29→\n    30→* AC bypass on bias nodes — makes them AC ground\n    31→Cbn vbn 0 1\n    32→Cbcn vbcn 0 1\n    33→Cbp vbp 0 1\n    34→Cbcp vbcp 0 1\n    35→\n    36→* Input with AC stimulus\n    37→Vinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val} ac 1\n    38→\n    39→* Loop-breaking: L=1GH passes DC, blocks AC. C holds vinn at DC for AC.\n    40→Lbreak vout vinn 1G\n    41→Cdc vinn 0 1\n    42→\n    43→* OTA\n    44→Xota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    45→CL vout 0 10p\n    46→\n    47→.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n    48→\n    49→.control\n    50→run\n    51→\n    52→* Compute measurements manually and echo in format verifier expects\n    53→* Note: vp() returns RADIANS in ngspice 42, verifier expects DEGREES\n    54→\n    55→* Peak gain\n    56→meas ac gain_peak_raw MAX vdb(vout)\n    57→\n    58→* Gain at specific frequencies\n    59→meas ac g1_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n    60→meas ac g10_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=10\n    61→meas ac g100_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\n    62→\n    63→* UGB and phase at UGB\n    64→meas ac ugb_raw WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n    65→meas ac phase_ugb_rad FIND vp(vout) WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n    66→\n    67→* Convert radians to degrees for the verifier\n    68→let phase_ugb_deg = phase_ugb_rad * 180 / 3.14159265359\n    69→\n    70→* Echo results in the exact format the verifier's parse_meas expects\n    71→echo \"gain_peak = $&gain_peak_raw\"\n    72→echo \"g1 = $&g1_raw\"\n    73→echo \"g10 = $&g10_raw\"\n    74→echo \"g100 = $&g100_raw\"\n    75→echo \"ugb = $&ugb_raw\"\n    76→echo \"phase_ugb = $&phase_ugb_deg\"\n    77→\n    78→quit\n    79→.endc\n    80→.end\n    81→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"893efe72-8d99-4982-a523-d2398e238a5c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T11:42:52.832Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_corner_tt.spice","content":"* TB: AC Open-Loop Analysis - TT Corner\n* Uses loop-breaking inductor technique\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\n\n* Self-biasing — tracks process corner\n* vbn: 500nA through diode-connected NMOS (same as M11)\nIbias_n vdd vbn dc 500n\nXbias_n vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.8u L=14u nf=1\n\n* vbcn: cascode reference — 263nA through stacked NMOS\nIbias_cn vdd vbcn dc 263n\nXbias_cn vbcn vbcn bias_mid 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1\nXbias_cs bias_mid vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=14u nf=1\n\n* vbp: 24.3nA through diode-connected PMOS (same as fold instance)\nIbias_p vbp 0 dc 24.3n\nXbias_p vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n\n* vbcp: cascode reference — 259nA through stacked PMOS\nIbias_cp vbcp 0 dc 259n\nXbias_cp vbcp vbcp pbias_mid vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\nXbias_fp pbias_mid vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n\n* AC bypass on bias nodes — makes them AC ground\nCbn vbn 0 1\nCbcn vbcn 0 1\nCbp vbp 0 1\nCbcp vbcp 0 1\n\n* Input with AC stimulus\nVinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val} ac 1\n\n* Loop-breaking: L=1GH passes DC, blocks AC. C holds vinn at DC for AC.\nLbreak vout vinn 1G\nCdc vinn 0 1\n\n* OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n\n.control\nrun\n\n* Compute measurements manually and echo in format verifier expects\n* Note: vp() returns RADIANS in ngspice 42, verifier expects DEGREES\n\n* Peak gain\nmeas ac gain_peak_raw MAX vdb(vout)\n\n* Gain at specific frequencies\nmeas ac g1_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\nmeas ac g10_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=10\nmeas ac g100_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\n\n* UGB and phase at UGB\nmeas ac ugb_raw WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\nmeas ac phase_ugb_rad FIND vp(vout) WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n\n* Convert radians to degrees for the verifier\nlet phase_ugb_deg = phase_ugb_rad * 180 / 3.14159265359\n\n* Echo results in the exact format the verifier's parse_meas expects\necho \"gain_peak = $&gain_peak_raw\"\necho \"g1 = $&g1_raw\"\necho \"g10 = $&g10_raw\"\necho \"g100 = $&g100_raw\"\necho \"ugb = $&ugb_raw\"\necho \"phase_ugb = $&phase_ugb_deg\"\n\nquit\n.endc\n.end\n","numLines":81,"startLine":1,"totalLines":81}}}
