{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01H7gTnf1HbF4Nn3hHsLJZG8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RT8NJfUYMJEqTBguGTPHQ5","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Fix bias with offset approach","prompt":"In /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/, update these 8 files with a new bias approach:\n- tb_corner_tt.spice, tb_corner_ss.spice, tb_corner_ff.spice, tb_corner_sf.spice, tb_corner_fs.spice\n- tb_temp_-40.spice, tb_temp_27.spice, tb_temp_85.spice\n\nRead each file first. Then replace the entire bias section (from \"* Self-biasing\" through the Cbcp line) with this new simpler bias:\n\n```\n* Self-biasing with voltage offsets — tracks process corner\n* vbn: 500nA through diode-connected NMOS (same as M11)\nIbias_n vdd vbn dc 500n\nXbias_n vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.8u L=14u nf=1\n\n* vbcn = vbn + 0.23V (cascode offset)\nVbcn_off vbcn vbn dc 0.23\n\n* vbp: 24.3nA through diode-connected PMOS (same as fold instance)\nIbias_p vbp 0 dc 24.3n\nXbias_p vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n\n* vbcp = vbp - 0.255V (cascode offset)\nVbcp_off vbp vbcp dc 0.255\n\n* AC bypass on self-biased nodes\nCbn vbn 0 1\nCbp vbp 0 1\n```\n\nThis replaces the old complex stacked bias (Ibias_cn, Xbias_cn, Xbias_cs, Ibias_cp, Xbias_cp, Xbias_fp, and all 4 bypass caps) with a simpler approach using voltage offsets for the cascode biases. Note: vbcn and vbcp don't need separate bypass caps because they're driven by voltage sources (zero AC impedance).\n\nUse the Edit tool on each file. The old text to replace starts with \"* Self-biasing\" and ends with \"Cbcp vbcp 0 1\" (inclusive)."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":877,"cache_read_input_tokens":241670,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":877},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inferen