{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FGJdqBjSdq9ShJfHsd6PFV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* TB: AC Open-Loop Analysis - Temperature 27C\n     2→* Uses loop-breaking inductor technique\n     3→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     4→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     5→.temp 27\n     6→\n     7→.param vdd_val = 1.8\n     8→.param vcm_val = 0.9\n     9→\n    10→Vdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\n    11→\n    12→* Self-biasing — tracks process corner\n    13→* vbn: 500nA through diode-connected NMOS (same as M11)\n    14→Ibias_n vdd vbn dc 500n\n    15→Xbias_n vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=3.8u L=14u nf=1\n    16→\n    17→* vbcn: cascode reference — 263nA through stacked NMOS\n    18→Ibias_cn vdd vbcn dc 263n\n    19→Xbias_cn vbcn vbcn bias_mid 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2u L=14u nf=1\n    20→Xbias_cs bias_mid vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8 W=2.15u L=14u nf=1\n    21→\n    22→* vbp: 24.3nA through diode-connected PMOS (same as fold instance)\n    23→Ibias_p vbp 0 dc 24.3n\n    24→Xbias_p vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=20u nf=1\n    25→\n    26→* vbcp: cascode reference — 259nA through stacked PMOS\n    27→Ibias_cp vbcp 0 dc 259n\n    28→Xbias_cp vbcp vbcp pbias_mid vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=0.42u L=2u nf=1\n    29→Xbias_fp pbias_mid vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8 W=4.5u L=20u nf=1\n    30→\n    31→* AC bypass on bias nodes — makes them AC ground\n    32→Cbn vbn 0 1\n    33→Cbcn vbcn 0 1\n    34→Cbp vbp 0 1\n    35→Cbcp vbcp 0 1\n    36→\n    37→* Input with AC stimulus\n    38→Vinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val} ac 1\n    39→\n    40→* Loop-breaking: L=1GH passes DC, blocks AC. C holds vinn at DC for AC.\n    41→Lbreak vout vinn 1G\n    42→Cdc vinn 0 1\n    43→\n    44→* OTA\n    45→Xota vinp vinn vout vdd 0 vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    46→CL vout 0 10p\n    47→\n    48→.ac dec 100 0.1 1G\n    49→\n    50→.control\n    51→run\n    52→\n    53→* Compute measurements manually and echo in format verifier expects\n    54→* Note: vp() returns RADIANS in ngspice 42, verifier expects DEGREES\n    55→\n    56→* Peak gain\n    57→meas ac gain_peak_raw MAX vdb(vout)\n    58→\n    59→* Gain at specific frequencies\n    60→meas ac g1_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n    61→meas ac g10_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=10\n    62→meas ac g100_raw FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\n    63→\n    64→* UGB and phase at UGB\n    65→meas ac ugb_raw WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n    66→meas ac phase_ugb_rad FIND vp(vout) WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n    67→\n    68→* Convert radians to degrees for the verifier\n    69→let phase_ugb_deg = phase_ugb_rad * 180 / 3.14159265359\n    70→\n    71→* Echo results in the exact format the verifier's parse_meas expects\n    72→echo \"gain_peak = $&gain_peak_raw\"\n    73→echo \"g1 = $&g1_raw\"\n    74→echo \"g10 = $&g10_raw\"\n    75→echo \"g100 = $&g100_raw\"\n    76→echo \"ugb = $&ugb_raw\"\n    77→echo \"phase_ugb = $&phase_ugb_deg\"\n    78→\n    79→quit\n    80→.endc\n    81→.end\n    82→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RT8NJfUYMJEqTBguGTPHQ5","session_id":"dc3cf414-60b5-4244-9a30-3b9794da6520","uuid":"b798257a-1f7e-42e5-a740-d6c9943a5c50","timestamp":"2026-03-23T11:45:38.645Z"}
